    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but isn't that kind of a circular argument though? you're saying we should intervene to stop atrocities, but only if we are prepared to commit to decades of nation-building and potentially infinite resources. if the only way to make it work is through a level of involvement that most countries aren't willing or able to sustain, isn't it basically just a fantasy? it feels like you're defending a doctrine that's impossible to actually execute properly.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
